### Which @angular/* package(s) are relevant/related to the feature request?

core

### Description

Many times we want to perform some specific operation on different events, like delay, debounceTime, throttle with current implementation it is not possible to do it with in template.


### Proposed solution

We can introduce, event pipes, similar to pipes in angular but which can be applied to events.

some thing like,

```html
<input (input | debounceTime : 300)="onInputChange()"
```
```typescript
@EventPipe({
name: 'debounceTime'
})
extend class DebounceTimeEventPipe  {
  handle<T>(obs: Observable<T>, arg: number) : Observable<T> {
    return obs.pipe(debounceTime(arg));
  }
}
```

### Alternatives considered

I think this can also be performed by custom `EventManager`/`EventManagerPlugin` but current default implementation provide limited options and are not easily extendable and also lack documentation.
